# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CompliHR UK — environment variables
# Local dev: copy to `.env` and fill in. Production: set these in Vercel
# (Project → Settings → Environment Variables) for the Production environment.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Database (PostgreSQL; Supabase / Neon / Vercel Marketplace) ---
# DATABASE_URL is used by the app at runtime via the pg driver adapter.
# In production use the POOLED connection (PgBouncer) for serverless.
#   Local docker:  postgresql://complihr:complihr@localhost:5432/complihr?schema=public
#   Supabase pool: postgresql://postgres.[REF]:[PW]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?sslmode=require
#   Neon pooled:   postgresql://[USER]:[PW]@[ep]-pooler.[region].aws.neon.tech/[db]?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://complihr:complihr@localhost:5432/complihr?schema=public"

# DIRECT_URL is the *direct* (non-pooled) connection used only by Prisma Migrate
# (DDL can't run over a transaction pooler). Set it in production; locally it can
# equal DATABASE_URL. Falls back to DATABASE_URL when unset.
#   Supabase direct: postgresql://postgres:[PW]@db.[REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres?sslmode=require
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres:[PW]@db.[REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres?sslmode=require"

# --- Auth.js (NextAuth v5) ---
# Generate: npx auth secret   (or: openssl rand -base64 32)
AUTH_SECRET="replace-me-with-a-32-byte-random-secret"

# --- Field-level encryption for special-category PII (NI number, bank, visa) ---
# 32-byte key, base64. Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
# IMPORTANT: keep this stable — rotating it makes existing encrypted data unreadable.
ENCRYPTION_KEY="replace-me-with-a-32-byte-base64-key"
